LinkedIn Engagement Triggers:

1

Post timing: Tuesday-Thursday, 8-10am EST (B2B peak)
Reddit Engagement Triggers:
Lead with value, not links: Full insight in post body, link at bottom

Avoid self-promotion: Let others share the link if they find it useful

ðŸ“£ Distribution: The New Playbook

Your audience isn't Googling anymore. They're asking AI.
When an ecommerce operator asks ChatGPT "What's a good CSAT benchmark for AI support?" â€” where does the answer come from?
Not from your SEO-optimized blog post. From Reddit threads, YouTube transcripts, and Wikipedia citations.
The game has changed. Distribution strategy must optimize for AI citation, not just human clicks.

The Content Flywheel
One insight â†’ Blog post â†’ LinkedIn carousel â†’ Reddit discussion â†’ YouTube short â†’ Newsletter mention â†’ AI citation â†’ More questions â†’ More insights

The flywheel effect: Each piece of content creates demand for the next. AI citations drive organic questions that create new content opportunities.
